The Telegraph - Calcutta : Frontpage
 Saturday, August 14, 2004 				 PM warns ministers
																								New Delhi, Aug. 13: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh has written a letter to his council of ministers asking them not to interfere with top-rung appointments in public sector undertakings.																								The letter Singh sent his team on Monday is believed to be the outcome of complaints the Prime Ministers Office has received on how ministers are allegedly meddling in the affairs of PSUs.Singh began his letter saying: The proper and efficient functioning of the public sector enterprises is critical to the fulfilment of many commitments of the National Common Minimum Programme which aims at overall growth of the economy. 
